About 145 Nigerians on Friday returned to the country from Sudan. Nigerians in Diaspora Commission, NIDCOM confirmed their arrival at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja. On its official Twitter page, NIDCOM wrote: “145 Nigerians arrive Nnamdi Azikiwe Int’l Airport, Abuja at about 12.45pm local time via Air Sudan today, Friday, 26th June 2020”. “All Evacuees will now proceed on 14 days self-isolation mandated by NCDC.” According to NCDC rules, the returnees would be tested on arrival and would go on compulsory 14-days isolation in line with the protocol for evacuation.